subject: Re: [junit] Testcases named 'unknown' in JUnit reports
msgSnippet: Einar, Ant 1.6.5 works with JUnit 3.8. JUnit 4 support is available in ant 1.7 alpha. Regards, Jan ... From: einarwh To: junit@yahoogroups.com Sent: Tuesday,
messageBody:
Einar,

Ant 1.6.5 works with JUnit 3.8.
JUnit 4 support is available in ant 1.7 alpha.

Regards, Jan



----- Original Message -----
From: einarwh
To: junit@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Tuesday, May 09, 2006 10:29 AM
Subject: [junit] Testcases named 'unknown' in JUnit
reports


Hi,

I'm a newbie trying to run my unit tests and generate
test reports
from ant. All my testcases seem to run just fine and
pass, but for
some reason, they end up as 'unknown' in the JUnit
reports! For
instance, the XML contains data like this:

<testcase
classname="junit.framework.JUnit4TestCaseFacade"
name="unknown" time="0.031" />

Any thoughts as to what I'm doing wrong?

I'm using (trying to use) JUnit 4.1 and ant 1.6.5 on a
Windows box.

Thanks,
Einar
